.TH "vsp1_dl_body_pool_create" 9 "vsp1_dl_body_pool_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vsp1_dl_body_pool_create \- Create a pool of bodies from a single allocation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct vsp1_dl_body_pool *" vsp1_dl_body_pool_create
.BI "(struct vsp1_device *vsp1 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_bodies "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_entries "  ","
.BI "size_t extra_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vsp1" 12
The VSP1 device
.IP "num_bodies" 12
The number of bodies to allocate
.IP "num_entries" 12
The maximum number of entries that a body can contain
.IP "extra_size" 12
Extra allocation provided for the bodies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a pool of display list bodies each with enough memory to contain the
requested number of entries plus the \fIextra_size\fP.

Return a pointer to a pool on success or NULL if memory can't be allocated.
